Cell.Text: [S] It's you! What are you doing here? Are you working for them? Tell me now!
I see, so you must be the Dragonborn. When I returned to the tavern, Eivind wasn't there, so I came back as soon as I could. He's likely furious with me right now.
I see, so you must be the Dragonborn then. I noticed you caused quite the ruckus amongst them while you were in there.

Node.Caption: _arcQuest002TelishaFGTopicCalder: No. I got your letter, then Eivind sent me here to find you.

Cell.Text: Both Calder, and his dog are alive.

By the divines. They had me locked up in that cage. | Calder helped me escape, so I hid myself. That's when I saw you enter, I've been waiting here ever since. | Despite his shortcomings, I'm surprised he had the spine, let alone moral substance to help me, one of his enemies, out of such a dire situation. | He's clearly not the man I thought he was. | I will now gladly have him attend The Four Shields moving forward, and share a drink with him in honor of his heroic actions today. | But...we haven't any time to waste right now, Eivind is probably worried about me, not to mention we've made ourselves an enemy of the bandits.
Calder is alive but...his dog didn't make it.
